entry.content:

yet as Ash on X11 backend can't import dmabufs, so passing

additional flag to disable gpu in Lacros running with ash

browser tests. Without disabling gpu, gpu process crashes

repeatedly before switching to software mode, and this

extra delay can cause tests to timeout.

entry.title: [DoH] Add metric to better report auto-upgrade success
entry.content:
This CL adds a new metric that reports the state of the insecure DNS

to secure DNS auto-upgrade process one minute after this process

begins. This should provide a more direct way of identifying whether

the auto-upgrade functionality should be enabled for a given provider.



Also, this CL extends the expiration times of several other metrics

that we are considering replacing by this new metric (and extends the

expiration of Net.DNS.DnsTransaction.SecureNotValidated...FailureError

to match the set of those metrics that we plan to keep longer term.)

entry.title: blink::ExternalCanvasResource: Use viz::TransferableResource
entry.content:
Most callers of ExternalCanvasResource::Create use an existing

TransferableResource to populate the create call's parameters. These

parameters are then used to populate the result of CanvasResource::

PrepareTransferableResource.



The goal of this change is to just pass the TransferableResource

around directly (rather than risk dropping parts of the structure,

e.g, the HDR metadata, during the round-trip).



Change ExternalCanvasResource to take the TransferableResource as a

parameter. Make CanvasResource::PrepareAcceleratedTransferableResource

be a virtual function, and make ExternalCanvasResource override it,

populating the output parameter with its TransferableResource.

entry.title: Use BackToBackFrameScheduler for web_tests with threaded compositing
entry.content:
With non-threaded compositing, main frames are scheduled via PostTask

and there is no delay -- tests run through main frames at the maximum

possible rate.



With threaded compositing, main frames run at the pace set by the

BeginFrameSource, which by default is a timer running at 60Hz. This

can cause tests to take much longer to run with threaded compositor,

if a test procedure runs for many main frames.



BackToBackFrameScheduler should cause web_tests running with the

threaded compositor to run *approximately* as fast as the non-threaded

case.



Bug: 770028

rolling basis. This will help ensure histograms that *should* be

deprecated *are*, and also avoids histograms expiring inadvertently

because someone missed an email.

entry.title: [CVV Storage] Fix UpdateCreditCard with updated empty CVC
entry.content:
Change the logic when new CVC is empty:

Delete CVC record if the new CVC is empty

Every time the new CreditCard's cvc is empty, we will delete the CVC

record, thus we can ensure that existing CVC records are not empty.

(empty CVC in read-out CreditCard object == empty CVC record)



Unchanged when new CVC is not empty:

Insert if old CVC empty (Empty CVC record)

Update if old CVC is not empty (We do have old record in webdatabase)



Problem:

User have a existing card, then user update the card with empty CVC, then user try to update the card CVC again, Chrome will crash.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vJs3wU8gmPReGITy9FoBhKQs7vwx_0Nv/view?usp=drive_link



Cause:

old_credit_card.cvc is empty doesn't mean it doesn't exist in local_stored_cvc table. We should not use old_credit_card.cvc is empty to determine the logic to insert or update cvc into local_stored_cvc table.

entry.title: Transfer system print dialog settings to Print Backend service
entry.content:
Linux and macOS platforms are not yet able to display the system print

dialog from the Print Backend service. In these cases the dialog is

still invoked from the browser process. This requires that the user

settings specified must be collected and then transferred to the

Print Backend service so that the rest of the print pipeline can still

be performed out-of-process.



The nature of such data is platform specific. Encapsulate the data

in a dictionary value for transfer to the service. Mojom validation

ensures that the data passes at least basic expectations for the number

and type of entries in the dictionary.
